			<p>I recently made a presentation to my company about Web 2.0. I was essentially guiding them through a &#8220;walking tour&#8221; of the web. I had wrestled with using Powerpoint or Keynote, and finally I just decided to build a <a href="http://del.icio.us/web20talk" rel="nofollow">delicious page for my talk</a>.</p>

<p>I realize it&#8217;s not appropriate for many presentations, but it was perfect for my purpose. I had this nice pages of links to point people to that weren&#8217;t able to attend, and the presentation itself exemplified what I was describing.</p>

<p>I also set up an internal Wiki page to continue the discussion after the presentation. People have been using it and the discussion has continued as I had hoped. For many, it&#8217;s their first experience with a Wiki and with this democratized web concept.</p>		</li>
		
		
	
